
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a target node. It retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] for specific keys like [limit], [offset], [order], and [direction], and appends these to the node referenced by the expression in [add]. The [add] slot is used to dynamically extend the node structure with additional data, allowing for flexible and dynamic data manipulation.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
